name: Bachelor
line: Cynthia...

line: I thought you'd never ask.

name: Morty
line: Oh, cool! Is that crystallized Zanthonite? It conducts electrons across dimensions.

name: Rick
line: 20% accurate, as usual,  Morty.  The important thing being I just upgraded our cable package with programming from every conceivable reality.

line: Wait, does that mean we get Showtime Extreme?

name: Rick
line: How about Showtime Extreme in a world where man evolved from corn?

line: We're not so different. We're both corn of action.

name: Summer
line: Bor-ing.

line: Summer,  you just spent  three months watching a man choose a fake wife.

name: Jerry

name: Rick
line: Jerry, you don't get it. This is infinite TV, from infinite universes. Look.

name: Glenn
line: This shit is delicious.

name: Rick
line: A movie about a guy eating shit.  A violent Antiques Show...

line: It's a pleasure to have you.

name: Jerry
line: The pleasure's all mine.

name: Jerry
line: Wait!

name: Beth
line: What in the hell?

name: Rick
line: I agree. Where's this going?

name: Jerry
line: No, the other thing! Go back!

name: Rick
line: Really? All right, fine.

name: Woman
line: Glenn, this is a court order. It says you can't eat shit anymore.

name: Rick
line: All right, Jerry, when you're right, you're right. Now I'm hooked.

line: Coming up next on "Shmloo's the Shmloss", Shmlony has a nightmare.

line: Shmlantha, Schmlona!

line: Schmlove, Schmlandula, Schmlonathan--

name: Rick

line: Go back, go back!

name: Rick
line: Jeez.

name: Jerry
line: You speak da tru-tru.

name: Jerry
line: I'm in "Cloud Atlas"! What's "Cloud Atlas"?

name: Jerry
line: Sometimes small tru-tru different than da big tru-tru.

name: Beth
line: How is this possible?

name: Rick
line: Infinite timelines, infinite possibilities - including a time line where Jerry's a movie star. Look, you guys are getting excited about the wrong aspect of this device. Ju-- Wa-- Look at this.

line: And now, another Quick Mystery.

name: Cop
line: I just want to know who could've done something like this. It's a travesty!

name: Killer 1
line: I did. See this knife and all the blood on it? Here's my fingerprints.

name: Judge
line: Guilty! I sentence you to life in prison.

name: Host in Trenchcoat
line: Here's another Quick Mystery.

line: My mother's dead!

line: Guilty! Sentenced to murder.

name: Host in Trenchcoat
line: Here's anothe--

name: Killer 3
line: I'm the killer!

name: Host in Trenchcoat
line: Wow, that one was really quick, wasn't it?

name: Rick
line: Now who wants to watch random, crazy TV shows from different dimensions, a-a-and then who wants to narcissistically obsess about their alternate self?

name: Beth, Summer, and Jerry
line: Narcissism. The narcisstic stuff. I want to obsess about myself.

name: Rick
line: Here.  These scan your retinas, and let you view parallel time lines through genetically matching versions of your eyes.  Go fetch!

name: Beth and Summer
line: Yes! This is so cool! Ladies First!

name: Rick
line: I'm proud of you, Morty.

name: Morty
line: Hey man, I don't give a crap about myself, Rick. Let's watch some crazy stuff, yo!

name: Ants-In-My-Eyes Johnson
line: I'm Ants-In-My-Eyes Johnson, Here at Ants-in-My-Eyes Johnson's Electronics. I mean, there's so many ants in my eyes! And there's so many TVs, microwaves, radios I think, I can't-- I'm not 100% sure what we have here in stock, because I can't see anything. Our prices, I hope, aren't too low! Check out this refrigerator! Only $200! What about this microwave? Only $100! That's fair! I'm Ants-in-My-Eyes Johnson! Everything's black, I can't see a thing!  And also I can't feel anything either-- did I mention that? But that's not as catchy as having ants in your eyes. So that always goes, you know, off by the wayside. I can't feel. It's a very rare disease. All my-- All my nerves, they don't allow for the sensation of touch. So I never know what's going on. Am I standing? Sitting? I don't know.

name: Beth
line: Are we sure we want to do this? Look at our own alternate lives?

name: Jerry
line: You're right. Maybe we should just play Yahtzee--  Give me those!

name: Beth
line: What do you see?

name: Jerry
line: Whiteness... Pure whiteness.

name: Johnny Depp
line: You're my best friend, Jerry Smith. I love doing cocaine with you.

name: Jerry
line: Whoa! I love doing cocaine with you too, Johnny Depp!

name: Beth
line: Haven't we spent enough time on you?  I'm performing surgery... but not on a horse, on a human!

name: Jerry
line: That's great, Beth! You always wanted to be a real surgeon.

name: Beth
line: I am a real surgeon.

name: Jerry
line: Ahh, uh-- Summer's turn!

name: Summer
line: Finally! I don't see anything.

name: Beth
line: Well, you should select a different timeline, I mean, if your father and I achieved our dreams, there's a chance you weren't even born-- That came out wrong, that came out very wrong.

name: Summer
line: Fine, I'll find a world where you bothered to have me.  We're playing Yahtzee.

name: Beth
line: Yahtzee's fun. We love Yahtzee.

name: Jerry
line: It's a fun game for fun families! Hey, could I get those goggles back for a second?

name: Announcer
line: It's a 45 horsepower with anti-lock brakes, and it's the official car of Mr. Sneezy 3D. It's the brand-new Sneezy XL. The horn when you honk it makes a sneeze noise.  It's polite, it's right, and it's Sneezy Deezy Mc-fucking Deluxe.

name: Mr. Sneezy 3D
line: Oh, I'm Mr. Sneezy! Achoo!

name: Morty
line: Huh, seems like TV from other dimensions has a somewhat looser feel to it.

name: Rick
line: Yeah, it's got an almost improvisational tone.

name: Announcer
line: It's in theaters now! Coming this summer: Two brothers. In a van. And then a meteor hit. And they ran as fast as they could, from giant cat monsters. And then a giant tornado came. And that's when things got knocked into 12th gear.

name: Beth
line: Holy crap, I am winning a Nobel Prize.

name: Jerry
line: Come on! Time's up!  I'm taming a lion! No, wait, uhh there are film cameras. I might be a lion-tamer in a movie.  You get the idea. I work with lions.

name: Summer
line: Ooh, we're not playing Yahtzee,  we're playing Chutes and Ladders. It seems like when I exist, life gets a little more, I don't know, predictable?

name: Beth
line: When two people create a life together, they set aside their previous lives as individuals.

name: Jerry
line: Gimme a break! We're not heroes for having unprotected sex on prom night.

name: Beth
line: Oh, I get it. Now that you know you could have had it better, you resent me for holding you back.

name: Jerry
line: Well now that we know you think the tables are turning, we know you thought there were unturned tables!

name: Beth
line: What are you talking about?

name: Jerry
line: All this time, you've been thinking, "What if that loser Jerry hadn't talked me out of the abortion?"

name: Summer
line: Um--

name: Jerry
line: Well now you know: you'd be a doctor.  Whoop-dee-doo. You'd also be drinking wine, alone in a house full of exotic birds. And I'd be on DiCaprio's yacht--  banging Kristen Stewart!

name: Summer
line: You thought about getting an abortion?

name: Beth
line: Everyone thinks about it. Obviously, I'm the version of me that didn't do it. So you're welcome.

name: Jerry
line: Yeah, you're welcome.

name: Summer
line: Yeah, thank you guys so much. It's a real treat to be raised by parents that force themselves to be together instead of being happy.

name: Rick
line: Hey, do we have any wafer cookies?  Mm!  Oh, boy. Looks like you guys have been checking out alternate lives and realizing you don't have it as good, huh? That's too bad. You know, me and Morty are having a blast, We just discovered a show called "Ball Fondlers". I mean, I don't want to rub it in or anything, but you guys clearly backed the wrong conceptual horse.

name: Rick
line: I'm in heaven right now.

name: Morty
line: This might be the best day of my life.

name: Beth
line: So now what do we do?

name: Jerry
line: That show "Ball Fondlers" sounded kind of interesting.

name: Summer
line: Dad!

name: Jerry
line: What? They're having fun in there! What do you guys want from me? Every family on this block has to wonder if they're together by choice. Our family just has inter-dimensional goggles to show us for a fact that we're not.

name: Summer
line: Well, I'm leaving!

name: Beth
line: You can't leave, you're 17!

name: Summer
line: Yeah, and I'm not pregnant. I'm gonna have better judgment than you guys had at my age. I'm gonna... move to the southwest and-- I don't know, do something with turquoise.

name: Announcer
line: It's Saturday Night Live! Starring A Piece of Toast! Two guys with handle-bar mustaches! A man painted silver who makes robot noises! Garmanarnar! Three s-- uh uh, uh, uh, I'll get back to that one. A hole in the wall, where the men can see it all, and returning, for his 25th consecutive year: Bobby Moynihan!

name: Rick
line: Interesting fun fact, uh… Moynihan and Piece of Toast hate each other. Apparently they've got some real creative differences.

name: Fake Doors Salesman
line: Hey, are you tired of real doors, cluttering up your house, where you open 'em, and they actually go somewhere?  And you go in another room? Get on down to "Real Fake Doors"! That's us. Fill a whole room up with 'em. See? Watch, check this out!  Won't open. Won't open. Not this one, not this one. None of 'em open! FakeDoors.com is our website, so check it out for a lot of really great deals on fake doooooooors!

line: Hey, wait a minute, Rick. Wh-- I thought this was a commercial. Wh-what's going on? I mean--

line: Relax, Morty. Don't-don't worry about it. Let's just just see where this goes.

line: Step on it, we all got places to be!  Son of a bitch!

line: See, that must be where he lives. OK...

name: Rick

line: We have fake doors like you wouldn't believe! What are you worried about? Come get fake doors. Call us up, and order some fake doors today. Don't even hesitate, Don't even worry and don't even...

line: Wait wait, Rick! Hold on hold on...

name: Fake Doors Salesman
line: ...give it a second thought. That's our slogan. See it on the bottom of the screen, below our name. Here's another slogan, right below that one. What are you worried about? Come get fake doors! Get in here quick, get out quicker, with an arm of fake doors in you arms.

name: Morty
line: Okay, okay, you can change it.

name: Fake Doors Salesman
line: Don't even worry about it!

line: I hate Mumunmunundsdays. And I really could go for some enchiladas.

name: Morty
line: Yeah hey, that's pretty, pretty that's true. That's right!

name: Gazorpazorpfield
line: You dumb, stupid, weak, pathetic, white, white uh, uh guilt, white guilt, milquetoast piece of human garbage.

line: Jeez, Gazorpazorpfield, that's-- you know you're pretty mean to me, but that takes the cake.

name: Gazorpazorpfield
line: I don't give a fuck! I'm Gazorpazorp-fucking-field, bitch!  Now give me my fucking enchiladas!

name: Morty

name: Rick
line: No, Morty, it's Lorenzo Music. In this reality, he's still alive.

name: Morty
line: Oh, okay, was his name Lorenzo Music?

name: Rick
line: Yeah, I'm pretty sure. He also did that voice of that one guy from Ghostbusters, which is really strange, because it's the same character Bill Murray played in the movie. But then, when they made the movie Bill Murray did the voice of Gazorpazorp-- or Garfield, I mean.

name: Morty
line: Yeah, that's pretty cool, Rick. So all that happened in this reality too?

name: Rick
line: I don't know. Just making conversation with you, Morty. What do you think? I-I-I-I know everything about everything?

name: Beth
line: Did you really talk me out of the abortion?

name: Jerry
line: Well, we... we blew a tire on the way to the clinic.

name: Beth
line: I think, in my head, I was doing it all for the kids. And now the first kid is going to... do something with turquoise.

name: Jerry
line: Which is either code for crystal meth, or a gateway to it.

name: Beth
line: So, we didn't do the kids any favors. So, we should stay together for each other and ourselves... or...

name: Jerry
line: Or?

name: Spokesman
line: Man. Woman. And now, trunk man? We know science has created men that have a trunk that allows them to have sex with both male and female partners. But we don't like the idea of these people getting married. Put a line in the sand everybody--, people! Vote no on proposition XW2.

name: New Yorker
line: Hey, let the trunk people have sex and get married, huh?

name: Spokesman
line: Paid for by... Trunk People.

line: Oh, I love me Strawberry Smiggles! Ooh, I hope nobody ever gets my hands on me, and tries to steal my Strawberry Smiggles. I'm going to eat every last one of them, because and then they'll be in my stomach, and nobody will ever be able to eat them. Except for me, because they're going to be all inside my stomach. I'm my name is Mister... Tophat Jones, and God forbid anyone ever take my sniggy, little pig-dul smiggles. I'm keeping 'em all for me.

name: Mr. Tophat Jones
line: No! Get away from me! Get away from me and my Strawberry Smiggles! No!   Jesus Christ! Jesus Christ! It hurts! My entrails are out! Why would you even want to eat these? They're-they're soaked with my stomach acid! Oh, Jesus Christ! Lord and savior and spirit! Save me! Take me to the light! Oh, my God, I see Demons! I see demons are coming!

name: Morty
line: Jeez, Rick. Oh my god! That's some pretty hardcore stuff, you know, for a cereal commercial.

name: Rick
line: Well, you know, Morty, I mean, you want to sell boxes of cereal, you gotta, you gotta, pump the gas a little. Pedal t-to the metal, Morty.

line: In a world, where muscular mannies are coming, and they're coming strong, there's only three unmuscular Michaels.

line: Get down! Hurry, run!

name: Announcer
line: And that's when real - Turbulent - Juice is coming, and you gotta take care of it. With Turbulent Juice, turbulent tables, no room is safe from the turbulent power of Turbulent Juice.

name: Morty
line: What in the hell?

name: Rick
line: Sex sells, Morty.

name: Morty
line: Sex sells what? W-was that a movie, or like, does it clean stuff?  Hey, Dad. W-w-what's going on?

name: Jerry
line: Oh, your mother and I are going to be spending some time apart, Morty. And your sister found out she was an unwanted pregnancy.

name: Morty
line: W-w-w-what?

name: Rick
line: Speaking of  what, Morty,  what should we  watch next? What about this?

name: Police Chief
line: Baby Legs, you're a good detective… but not good enough, because of your baby legs. So I'm partnering you up with Regular Legs.

name: Regular Legs
line: Hey there.

name: Baby Legs
line: Detective, I'm-- this is upsetting to me, because I feel like I don't need no regular-leg partner.

name: Police Chief
line: Baby Legs, don't talk back to me. Good luck you two, there's a criminal to kill.

name: Regular Legs
line: Wow! You sure found this guy quick!

name: Baby Legs
line: Uh, yeah, because I'm a good detective.

name: Regular Legs
line: Look, Baby Legs, it's the criminal!

name: Criminal
line: Oh, fuck it, I'm the killer. I'm running, running real quick.

name: Baby Legs
line: Baby Legs, here we go!  That's the sound I make, when I'm trying to run fast.  All right, I'm not going to get him. I'm, I-I just learned a real valuable lesson.

name: Regular Legs
line: I'm coming, Baby Legs! I'm Regular Legs!  We got him!

name: Baby Legs
line: Hey, that was good team work.

name: Police Chief
line: Baby Legs, and Regular Legs, I'm proud of you two for working together, and Baby Legs, I know it was hard for you to come to the conclusion that you need a partner. But I'm proud of you that you did it.

name: Baby Legs
line: Hey thanks, chief!

name: Police Chief
line: Now get the fuck out of here!

name: Rick
line: Pretty cool, huh, Morty?  Oh.

name: Jerry
line: Uh, I thought it was cool.

name: Rick
line: I don't give a fuck what you think, Jerry.

name: Morty
line: Hey, uh Y-Y-Y-You doin' okay? I-I-I kind of know how you feel, Summer.

name: Summer
line: No, you don't. You're the little brother. You're not the cause of your parents' misery. You're just a symptom of it.

name: Morty
line: Can I show you something?

name: Summer
line: Morty, no offense, but a drawing of me you made when you were 8 isn't gonna make make me feel like less of an accident.

name: Morty
line: That, out there? That's my grave.

name: Summer
line: Wait, what?

name: Morty
line: On one of our adventures, Rick and I basically destroyed the whole. World. So, we bailed on that reality, and we came to this one. Because in this one, the world wasn't destroyed. And in this one, we were dead. So we came here, a-a-and we buried ourselves, and we took their place. And every morning, Summer, I eat breakfast 20 yards away from my own - rotting - corpse.

name: Summer
line: So, you're not my brother?

name: Morty
line: I'm better than your brother. I'm a version of your brother you can trust when he says, "Don't run". Nobody exists on purpose. Nobody belongs anywhere. Everybody’s gonna die. Come watch TV?

name: Announcer
line: Mrs. Sullivan always planned to leave everything to her cats. But sometimes, plans need a helping paw. What are the kitties to do, but buckle together and work as a team.

name: Business Man
line: Mrs. Sullivan, I uh, please forgive me for being forward, but your eyes are so beautiful!

name: Jerry
line: Wait, this is an actual movie?

name: Announcer
line: This fall, sparks will fly!

name: Business Man
line: Mrs. --Ooh, Sullivan-- ohh...

name: Announcer
line: Between one guy, who can't get a break...

name: Business Man
line: There's something about you, Mrs. Sullivan.

name: Announcer
line: ...and nine cats who break all the rules. Last Will and Testa-meow: Weekend at Dead Cat Lady's House 2.

name: Jerry
line: Well, somebody in Hollywood just lost their job.

name: Announcer
line: Written and directed by Jerry Smith.

name: Jerry
line: I wrote and directed that? What am I, nuts?

name: Rick
line: Hey Morty, you just missed a preview for your Dad's "Citizen Kane".

name: Morty
line: Doesn't matter.

name: Jerry
line: Hey, if your, uh, mother and I had to split custody - who would you guys choose?

name: Summer
line: Doesn't matter.

name: Jerry
line: Oh...

line: Breaking News: Academy Award-winning actor Jerry Smith is leading police on a slow-speed pursuit after suffering an apparent breakdown.

name: Jerry
line: Don't even think about it.

name: Rick
line: Come on, Je- Are you kidding me, Jerry? It's just a bunch of dumb tabloid crap.

name: Jerry
line: It's my life, and we're watching it.

name: Beth
line: You did it, Beth. You really nailed it. You're a surgeon. A human surgeon. Yay you win.

name: Jerry
line: Where the hell am I going?

name: Rick
line: What are you asking me for Jerry?  I'm sitting here  trying to figure out why the cops don't just take you out. Th--  they've got a clear shot to your head. I can't believe our tax dollars pay for this.

name: Beth
line: Jerry? J-Jerry Smith?

name: Jerry
line: Beth Sanchez, I have been in love with you since high school. I hate acting, I hate cocaine, I hate Kristen Stewart. I wish you hadn't gotten that abortion, and I've never stopped thinking about what might've been.

name: Rick
line: Hey, Ball Fondlers? Huh? Ball Fondlers?

name: Summer
line: Yeah, I could go for some Ball Fondlers.

name: Morty
line: Yeah, Ball Fondlers.

line: Ha-ha, Hamster-in-Butt-World Weather is done, and now it's sports time, coming up.

name: Female Hamster
line: Oh, hello there!

name: Male Hamster
line: Good day to you, Miss.

name: Beth
line: So, the hamsters live inside the rectums of those people?

name: Rick
line: Yeah, sweetie, they-- that's where they live.

name: Jerry
line: Well, how does that work? I mean, do the butts look like little apartments inside?

name: Morty
line: Yeah! And can they like, leave the butt, and like walk around on their own?

name: Rick
line: Look, I don't know! I'm watching the-- same thing you guys are.

name: Summer
line: Grandpa Rick, if they leave the butt, and the person wanders off, how would they find their butt person again?

name: Rick
line: I don't know, Summer! I can't even hear the TV!  All right, that's it. We're just gonna go there, so you idiots can ask your stupid questions all day.

line: Ooh! Family vacation!
